## Ingredients
- 1 tsp oil
- 2 tbsp cashews, chopped
- 2 cups potatoes, cubed
- 1 tsp lemon juice
- ¼ tsp cumin seeds
- ¼ tsp coriander seeds
- ¼ cup red onion, chopped
- 1 green chilli, finely chopped
- ¾ tsp turmeric
- ½ tsp ground cumin
- ½ tsp ground coriander
- ¼ tsp cayenne (to taste)
- 2 tsp minced ginger
- ½ tsp garlic powder
- ½ tsp salt
- ½ tsp chaat masala or amchur
- ⅓ cup water
- ¼ cup green peas
- 2 tbsp chopped coriander
- 2 tbsp chopped mint
- 1 sheet puff pastry
- Optional greens or chutney for serving

## Method
1. Heat the oil and toast the cumin and coriander seeds until fragrant.
2. Add the onion, chilli, and cashews; cook until softened.
3. Stir in the spices, ginger, and garlic powder.
4. Add the potatoes, salt, and water; cook until tender.
5. Mash some potatoes for texture, then mix in the peas, herbs, and lemon juice.
6. Let the filling cool slightly.
7. Roll the puff pastry to double its size and place the filling on one half.
8. Fold the pastry over, seal the edges, and cut steam vents.
9. Bake at 200°C for 18–22 minutes until golden.
10. Cool slightly before slicing and serving.

## Notes
- Use a vegan puff pastry to keep the recipe plant-based.
- Can add other vegetables to the filling for variety.
- Store leftovers in the fridge and reheat before serving.
- Adjust spice levels according to preference.
